          <declname>c0</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>given a closed loop of edges, splits the surface along that loop so that after return: 1) returned loop has the same size as input, with corresponding edges in same indexed elements of both; 2) all edges of c0 have no left faces; 3) all returned edges have no right faces; Generated from function <computeroutput>MR::cutAlongEdgeLoop</computeroutput>. Parameter <computeroutput>topology</computeroutput> can not be null. It is a single object. Parameter <computeroutput>c0</computeroutput> can not be null. It is a single object. Never returns null. Returns an instance allocated on the heap! Must call <computeroutput>MR_std_vector_MR_EdgeId_Destroy()</computeroutput> to free it when you&apos;re done using it. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
